      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (mean relative error or equivalent) less than 15 % for NIH across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean relative error across 5 operating points is 8.3 %, with maximum error of 12.7 % at the highest flow-speed combination. All predictions fall within the experimental uncertainty band (±15 %). The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is met for the worst-case geometry variant."
