      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the quantities of interest. NIH is the standard regulatory metric for pump-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance. RH < 1 directly supports the predicate device comparison decision. Both QoIs are clinically and regulatorily relevant."
