      "rationale": "Validation is performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump, which is the same device family as the COU subject. Blood analog fluid (glycerin-water mixture matching viscosity of 35 % hematocrit blood) is used in experiments. Operating points span the same 2–6 L/min and 1500–3500 RPM ranges as the COU. Validation activities are directly relevant."
